                            <comment id="13600473" author="jochen@apache.org" created="Tue, 12 Mar 2013 21:07:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, but I disagree.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If an abstract class (or, an interface) isn&apos; Serializable, the subclasses (or implementations) can still choose to be. OTOH, you can&apos;t make a subclass Non-Serializable.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13600521" author="sauvage" created="Tue, 12 Mar 2013 21:49:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok you&apos;re right. What about make common subclasses Serializable ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
